Privacy Policy
Last Updated: March 2025

1. Introduction
Welcome to BillyAI ("we," "our," or "us"). We value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your information when you use our mobile application.

2. Information We Collect
We collect and process the following types of data:

a. Invoice Data
Information extracted from scanned or uploaded invoices, including IBAN, recipient name, payment reference (omschrijving), and payment value.
b. Camera and Images
If you use the app‚Äôs camera feature, we collect invoice images for scanning and processing only.
The images are processed locally and via Google Vision API to extract invoice details.
We do not store these images permanently.
c. Device Information
Non-personal data such as device type, operating system, and unique identifiers, collected solely for app performance optimization and analytics.
d. Usage Data
Information about how you interact with the app, such as features accessed and time spent using the app.
3. How We Use Your Information
Your data is used exclusively for the following purposes:

Extracting invoice details using OCR (Optical Character Recognition) and AI-powered processing.
Displaying extracted data in an easy-to-copy format.
Enhancing user experience through anonymized analytics.
Ensuring app functionality and performance optimization.
We do not use your data for advertising or tracking purposes.

4. Use of Cloud Services and Third-Party APIs
To provide accurate invoice data extraction, our app utilizes:

Google Vision API ‚Äì Converts images into readable text.
OpenAI API ‚Äì Analyzes OCR text to extract structured invoice details.
These APIs process your data temporarily but do not store or retain any information after processing.

5. Data Storage and Security
Your invoice details are securely stored in Firebase Firestore, linked to an anonymous identifier (not personal data).
Images captured using the camera feature are not stored‚Äîthey are processed and then discarded.
We implement industry-standard security measures, including encryption and anonymization, to protect your data.
We do not share or sell your personal information.
6. Permissions Requested by the App
To ensure the app functions properly, we require the following permissions:

Camera Access üì∑

Used exclusively for scanning invoices.
No images are stored after processing.
Storage Access (Temporary) üíæ

Used to handle invoice images during processing.
Files are not stored permanently on your device.
These permissions are only activated when needed and are never used for any other purpose.

7. Data Sharing
We do not sell your data. However, we share limited information with the following trusted service providers:

Google (Firebase, Vision API) ‚Äì Used for OCR processing and app functionality.
OpenAI API ‚Äì Used for extracting structured invoice data.
Additionally, we may disclose data if required by law or to comply with regulatory obligations.

8. Data Retention and Deletion
Invoice data is stored only while using the app.
Images are not stored after processing.
Data linked to anonymous identifiers remains in our system until you manually delete invoices.
You can request data deletion at any time via holidizer@gmail.com.
